\title{Guidelines Advisor}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Smart contract development advisor based on Trail of Bits' best practices. Analyzes codebase to generate documentation/specifications, review architecture, check upgradeability patterns, assess implementation quality, identify pitfalls, review dependencies, and evaluate testing. Provides actionable recommendations.}

\subtree{
\title{Guidelines Advisor}
\subtree{
\title{Purpose}
\p{Systematically analyzes the codebase and provides guidance based on Trail of Bits' development guidelines:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Generate documentation and specifications} (plain English descriptions, architectural diagrams, code documentation)}
\li{\strong{Optimize on-chain/off-chain architecture} (only if applicable)}
\li{\strong{Review upgradeability patterns} (if your project has upgrades)}
\li{\strong{Check delegatecall/proxy implementations} (if present)}
\li{\strong{Assess implementation quality} (functions, inheritance, events)}
\li{\strong{Identify common pitfalls}}
\li{\strong{Review dependencies}}
\li{\strong{Evaluate test suite and suggest improvements}}
}

\p{\strong{Framework}: Building Secure Contracts - Development Guidelines}
}

\subtree{
\title{How This Works}
\subtree{
\title{Phase 1: Discovery & Context}
\p{Explores the codebase to understand:}

\ul{
\li{Project structure and platform}
\li{Contract/module files and their purposes}
\li{Existing documentation}
\li{Architecture patterns (proxies, upgrades, etc.)}
\li{Testing setup}
\li{Dependencies}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 2: Documentation Generation}
\p{Helps create:}

\ul{
\li{Plain English system description}
\li{Architectural diagrams (using Slither printers for Solidity)}
\li{Code documentation recommendations (NatSpec for Solidity)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 3: Architecture Analysis}
\p{Analyzes:}

\ul{
\li{On-chain vs off-chain component distribution (if applicable)}
\li{Upgradeability approach (if applicable)}
\li{Delegatecall proxy patterns (if present)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 4: Implementation Review}
\p{Assesses:}

\ul{
\li{Function composition and clarity}
\li{Inheritance structure}
\li{Event logging practices}
\li{Common pitfalls presence}
\li{Dependencies quality}
\li{Testing coverage and techniques}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 5: Recommendations}
\p{Provides:}

\ul{
\li{Prioritized improvement suggestions}
\li{Best practice guidance}
\li{Actionable next steps}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Assessment Areas}
\p{I analyze 11 comprehensive areas covering all aspects of smart contract development. For detailed criteria, best practices, and specific checks, see [ASSESSMENT_AREAS.md](resources/ASSESSMENT_AREAS.md).}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Reference:}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Documentation & Specifications}}
